      "writtenOn": "2026-07-23T01:18:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thanks for the feedback.\n\nCurrently, the nvidia-gpu daemon queries all MCTP endpoints on D-Bus whenever an `NvidiaMctpVdm` node is present in the EM configuration. At runtime, it sends an MCTP VDM QueryDeviceIdentification command to each endpoint and dynamically discovers the device type (GPU, SMA, CX9 PCIe, etc.) from the response.\n\nBecause device discovery and type identification happen dynamically over MCTP rather than being declared per EID in the EM config, a single NvidiaMctpVdm entry causes all NSM-capable devices on the bus to be monitored.\n\nIn our target platform, multiple devices support NSM (e.g., SMA and CX9), but we only intend to monitor SMA at this stage.\n\nIf compile-time options aren\u0027t preferred, would you suggest extending the NvidiaMctpVdm EM configuration schema (e.g., adding an optional property like SupportedDeviceTypes or EnablePcie: false) so filtering can be driven at runtime by EM config instead?",
      "parentUuid": "aaa9091d_bdc5d0ae",
      "revId": "b56cc99844e7a136595da029aff22535e531ca85",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
